Lambda Expressions can be used to represent the instances of functional interfaces. 

Syntax: 

- (args) -> logic;

- (args) -> {
  logic;
  return a;
}

Types of Lambda Parameters:

There are three Lambda Expression Parameters are mentioned below:

1) Lambda with Zero Parameter: () -> System.out.println("Zero parameter lambda");
2) Lambda with Single Parameter: (p) -> System.out.println("One parameter: " + p);
3) Lambda with Multiple Parameters: (p1, p2) -> System.out.println("Multiple parameters: " + p1 + ", " + p2);

interface Calculator {
    int operation(int a, int b);
}
class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        
        Calculator add = (a, b) -> a + b;
        Calculator sub = (a, b) -> a - b;
        Calculator mul = (a, b) -> a * b;
        Calculator div = (a, b) -> a / b; 
        
        System.out.println(add.operation(3, 4));
        System.out.println(sub.operation(4, 3));
        System.out.println(mul.operation(3, 4));
        System.out.println(div.operation(4, 3));
    }
}